node.text:
After both of their siblings died and weeks of quarantine, Woody and Ethel finally met! Not sure it was the epic love story we all imagined 😂

Sweet little Woody is growing up, he was neutered and microchipped last Friday and he heads to his forever home at the end of next week! There might be tears on my end.

Until then, he has Ethel to keep him on his toes!

#IndianSpringsKitties #fosteringsaveslives #adoptdontshop #spayandneuter #LucyAndEthelKittkes #fosterkittens #catsofinstagram #kittens

node.text:
Poor Ethel misses her sister. I really want to put her in with Woody but I’m so strict on quarantine. I just wonder if she could have anything she could pass to him. I doubt it. She’s displaying zero symptoms of being ill.

Until then, she’s taking comfort in Grandma Blanche’s favorite bed.

Thank you for all the messages of love and support. I’m always hesitant to share the bad parts of fostering because I never want to discourage anyone from fostering.  We take in the most critical cases to foster. Not all kittens are this complicated and need this much care. There are easy foster kitties out there that just need a safe place to stay temporarily until they are ready for adoption.

#fosterkitten #LucyAndEthelKitties

Thank you to all who donated to make this happen and thank you most of all to @greatergoodcharities and @iheartcatscom

node.text:
You definitely don’t need an entire room to be able to foster kittens. A spare bathroom, a pet playpen or even an extra large dog kennel works great.

I also don’t give kittens access to things that I can’t easily disinfect or throw away (more expensive cat scratchers or cat condos) until I know they are healthy. I make sure that they don’t have anything they can spread (diarrhea, fungus, URI, etc.) before I give them access to these things.

node.text:
Mama Sprinkle’s babies are 6-weeks old and as you can see they are full of playful energy! I’m so happy to bring Grandma Blanche’s quilt into their room. It brought her joy and it’s only fitting to have with these joyful babies.

Thank you to @parkandbench for this awesome boom box scratcher! It’s a big hit with the kitties and mama likes to hide out inside.

#RainyDayKitties #fosterkittens #fosteringsaveslives #catscratcher #pawsneedclaws #kittens #6weeksold #instacute #cattoys #kitties

node.text:
Truffle and Shiitake have moved from the kennels to the big kid foster room!

Please don’t think you need to have a dedicated room for fosters. A pet playpen, spare bathroom or XL dog kennel works just fine.

I have their sister Portabella separated in the pet playpen and Chickadee is in my spare bathroom.

I walked in on these two and caught them playing. Now I’ll get to sit in their room and see if I can get them to play with me! I think I should go LIVE tomorrow so you can all join me!

#fungusamonguskitties #fosterkittens kittens #adoptdontshop #whitekitten #catsofinstagram #adoptdontshop #spayandneuter

node.text:
READY FOR A FAMILY!

We’ve been working a lot with little Portobella. She loves to be held and cuddled. She really loves playing with toys. She is still skittish and will hiss when you approach her, but the minute you pick her up, she melts and starts to purr.

She needs a loving home that will continue to allow her to blossom. I think she would be good with another cat or on her own as long as someone is home with her to give her love and attention.

She is about 4-months-old and already spayed and vaccinated.

If you are in Las Vegas or willing to travel here to adopt, click on the link in my bio to complete an adoption inquiry form. She can also be transported to Southern California!

#adoptme #fosterkitten #adoptdontshop #spayandneuter #fungusamonguskitties #kitten #cutekitty #gato #kittylove

node.text:
Hhm. #pattingworks

(See previous post)

#3HotsandaCot #fosteringsaveslives #catsofinstagram #fungusamonguskitties #fosterkitten #adoptme #adoptdontshop

Check out Portobella!

We have had her separated from her siblings because she was the spiciest. We put her in a large playpen to gently push her out of her comfort zone. We’ve had her upstairs in the loft area so every time we walk by, she sees us and and took away anything that allowed her to hide away from us. 3 hots and a cot 😜

This is allowed her to get used to household noises. She hears the washer and dryer, vacuum and dogs barking. She’s been hissing at us anytime we go to pick her up so I pick her up with a blanket. In this video you will see my husband approaching her over and over again to get used to a hand coming towards her. It’s working! She’s coming out of her shell.

No more wrapping her in a burrito now, she has progressed to a tostada!

She still cannot have access to the entire house because I want to discourage hiding eventually, she will get there.

She also has no visible ringworm lesions like her brother does but has still been receiving regular antifungal baths as a precaution and all her bedding is washed frequently.

I’d say we’re pretty close to finding her a forever home! It’s going to need to be with someone who’s willing to continue to allow her to blossom, but she’s making excellent progress!

#fosterkitten #fosteringsaveslives #adoptdontshop #fungusamonguskitties

node.text:
C5 FUNDRAISER!

I love sharing my C5 photos and adventures. It’s such a great feeling to go in a trap/neuter all the cats in a colony and know that no more kittens will be born to suffer and/or die after being born outside.

C5 is an all-volunteer organization that is completely ran out of a 2-car garage. Since it’s inception in 2009, they have helped to lower the euthanasia rate at the municipal shelter by approximately 90%. Less kittens born on the street, means less kittens entering the shelter.

I have set a goal to raise $4,000 for C5. I know it’s a hefty goal, but I’m hoping that those who are able to give can. Even donating just $5 is greatly appreciated!

I was contacted recently by a generous anonymous donor who would like to donate $600 if we are able to raise the first $600.

Can you help?

Here is the link to the fundraiser:

https://mtyc.co/yzs7ff

I’ll add it to my Instagram stories as well.

Little Truffle thanks you! He was trapped and neutered by C5! @c5tnrlv

#trapneuterreturn #spayandneuter #fundraiser #pleaseshare #fungusamonguskitties

node.text:
HAPPY DAY!

Please help me in congratulating former foster Esmé (fka Peanut #peanutbutterandjed) who is officially now CURED from #FIP!

After 84 days of daily injections and an 84-day observation period, former foster Esmé is CURED!

I would like to thank her wonderful family (@__commetuveux) for not only providing this treatment for being diligent about her treatment and care. Thank you also to those who sent gifts to help chip in for her medication. Every kitty should be so fortunate as to have such a loving, committed home.

It’s very bittersweet thinking about all those who have lost the battle to FIP, but I am so grateful there is now treatment and a cure! A big shoutout to the #FIPwarrior community for paving the way for this live-saving treatment. #FIPsurvivor #fiptreatment

Portobella! Who knew that it could be spelled with an “o” or an “a”! Or maybe our Italian friends will school us once they wake up and see this post. Ahywhoo…we are going with Portabella with the nickname being Bella.

She is the spiciest of the three little fungis so I have her separated from the other two. I like to do that with hissy kittens since they tend to lean on one another as a crutch and won’t bond with people when they have one another around.

As far as her ringworm is concerned though, it appears to be very minor with only one questionable spot on her back. I’m still giving her regular baths with antifungal shampoo just as a precaution.

She also thinks that with her entire three months of life on earth she can outsmart me. Little does she know, I’m hip to her shenanigans.
